  return (...args) => {
    clearTimeout(timer);
    timer = setTimeout(() => fn(...args), delay);
  };
}

searchInput.addEventListener('input', debounce((e) => {
  fetchResults(e.target.value);
}, 300));
```

Each keystroke resets the timer. The function only executes once the user pauses for 300ms.

